He will understand the language of God more imperfectly than if he had not determined to ignore some of the facts in which it is written, but he will understand enough to know that the attitude of God is blessing. His is not a living but a dying theology, because that part of his world which his belief does not attempt to explain is ever encroaching with a larger and larger demand.
